&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caring for Children and Young People&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Children’s Emergency Department &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Play Worker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 3&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;1.2 WTE&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Children’s Emergency Department provides a welcoming and child friendly atmosphere, with toys, books, a television and a play area for children. The department is open 24 hours a day and sees in excess of 150 children per day at its busiest time. The unit is staffed by a team of experienced children’s nurses and Doctors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are now looking for a suitable applicant who has experience in working with children to join the team. The ideal candidate needs to be a fun and self-motivated person, who would enjoy the challenges of working in a busy fast-paced department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to provide a creative, stimulating and imaginative experience for children of all ages and meet the needs of children with special needs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for the right candidate to join the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameClare GrayJob titleSisterEmail addressclaregray1@nhs.netTelephone number02083333138Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candia St Clair&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister&lt;/p&gt;
